    Note: 2. Parse loop variable
    Let loop_variable be proc parse_identifier with parser
    If loop_variable is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Expected loop variable after 'For' keyword", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Return 0
    End If

    Note:
    2b. Optional loop-variable type annotation in the typed for-each form
    `For Each <var> as <Type> in <collection>:` (mirrors the monolith
    parser_parse_for_range_statement, parser.runa:7497-7511). The declared
    element type is consumed here; the HIR for-loop lowering derives the
    iterator's element type from the iterable expression itself
    (lower_for_statement / get_iterable_element_type), which is the canonical
    source of the loop-variable type, so the annotation is redundant for
    lowering and is consumed without changing the For AST shape. A qualified
    `.Type` suffix and a generic `[...]` suffix are absorbed for completeness.
