    If return_consumed is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Expected 'Return' keyword at start of Return statement", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: 2. Parse optional return value
    Let value be 0
    Let current_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
    Let token_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with current_token

    Note:
    Check whether a return value follows. A bare `Return` is terminated by a
    block / statement boundary: NEWLINE, EOF, `End` (End Process / End If / ...),
    or `Otherwise` (the close of an If-then branch). None of these begin a
    return-value expression. TOKEN_OTHERWISE must be in this terminator set — a
    valueless `Return` immediately before `Otherwise:` previously fell through and
    tried to parse the `Otherwise` keyword as the return value, desyncing the
    enclosing If-then block (surfaced downstream as "body statement: Otherwise").
    The set is a terminator blacklist (not an expression-head whitelist) on
    purpose: parse_primary_expression special-cases leading unary `-`
    (TOKEN_MINUS, classed binary in the precedence table) and word-form
    `negative`, which is_expression_head does NOT report, so a whitelist would
    wrongly drop the value from `Return -1` / `Return negative N` and change
    self-host codegen. The blacklist leaves every existing `Return <expr>` parse
    untouched and only reclassifies the `Otherwise` follow-token as "no value".
    :End Note
    If token_type is not equal to TOKEN_NEWLINE:
        If token_type is not equal to TOKEN_EOF:
