    End If

    Note: 3. Parse type name. Canonical Runa writes the declaration name as a
    Note: quoted STRING literal -- `Type called "Pt":` -- exactly as Process and
    Note: Protocol declarations do. parse_process_name accepts both the canonical
    Note: string-literal form and a bare identifier (for resilience) and builds a
    Note: uniform identifier node; parse_identifier rejects the string form, which
